HEADWORD: Thermotank
<hw>Ther"mo*tank</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + <ets>ank</ets>.]</ety> <def>A tank containing
pipes through which circulates steam, water, air, or the like, for
heating or cooling; -- used in some heating and ventilation
systems.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermotaxic</ent>⟦br⟧
